{
  "title": [
    "until"
  ],
  "description": "looping mechanism",
  "origin": "vanilla",
  "categories": [
    "Data Math",
    "Logic"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "bang",
          "description": "starts the loop"
        },
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "set number of iterations in the loop"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "bang",
          "description": "stops the loop"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "bang",
          "description": "bangs in a loop"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [],
  "body": "The until object's left inlet starts a loop in which it outputs \"bang\" until its right inlet gets a bang which stops it. If you start \"until\" with a number,  it iterates at most that number of times,  as in the Max \"uzi\" object."
}